node.text:
FULL video in Bio 🤙🏾🤙🏾 
What a treat it was to spend so much time on the north shore this year and score some pumping waves. Thanks to everyone for sharing the waves, clips, and @ryanperry for the edit 🤘🏾🤘🏾 #northshore #hawaii #surfing #connercoffin #grateful

node.text:
Down days on the north shore playing music! I’ve been into music and surfing since I was a little kid in a lot of ways from my dad turning me onto both. Music has been a super good creative outlet and feels super similar to surfing. Thanks for the down day video @peterkingphoto / @jamhouseofficial 
#transacoustic

node.text: I wrote this song a while back, but it feels particularly relevant right now during these bizarre times of covid-19 and self isolation. I’ve never shared songs that I’ve written, but am excited to take this time to work on existing pieces and write new music. ✌🏽 and ❤️

node.text: Just finished reading a book about the allman brothers which turned me on to this old carter family Tune that they used to jam. Was really really sad to hear about Neal Casal passing this week, so this ones for him. An amazing player who carried the torch of the music I love and was an even better person that seemed to have such a positive influence on people around him. If you’re struggling on the inside reach out to a friend or someone for a helping hand 🙌🏽🙌🏽❤️❤️

node.text: Sound on for this one! With the world title event around the corner, I thought I’d share this wave from the @nssasurf open boys final in 2005 at lower trestles and a little story. It’s crazy to think that this is where my surf career really started and now it’s going full circle for a chance at a world title! It’s been a good ride! I was a chunky little kid with a bowl cut who was just hitting puberty and i sure as shit was not supposed to win a stacked final at nationals. My parents didn’t know shit about surf contests but they were so damn supportive (so grateful for their support) of @parkercoffin’s and i passion for it and we had a lot of fun (and at times, quite interesting) family weekends spent on the beach. I loved surfing so much and mostly started competing because parker was good at it and as an older brother I wanted to try to keep up with him 🤷🏽‍♂️🙄 This final was stacked and in typical lowers fashion, it went flat! In the last couple of minutes I found myself out the back with this perfect left coming right to me. I pretty much only surfed rincon so even I was shocked when I tagged a few decent turns. You can hear my parents, grandparents, and close friends go ballistic with each turn. I still think they cheer this loud when I ride waves today 😂🙌🏾 huge thanks to @dalwaves for this clip and for supporting me since before I can remember. Him and Toma showed me so much but mostly were great humans to look up to.

I threw everything at it, but came up short. Fired up to have one last crack at the 2021 season at lowers in a couple weeks!!!! Hope to see you guys down there. 
@wsl ⁣

May be an image of text that says 'Connor Coffin fell short to Leo in the quarters but managed to smash his acoustic guitar into the back of Griffin Colapinto's head. Connor got enough points this comp to take Griffin's spot at Trestles, stripping him of the opportunity to win a world title at home. I'd love to share my feelings on this, but this less than appropriate YouTube comment does enough: David Burroughs Connor winning lowers would be like a white guy dunking in the NBA Since I definitely won't be allowed to do this again, I'll leave my last competitive surf opinion here:'.

node.text:
@stab thanks for your continued “premium” journalism, you could spell my name right 😂. It pissed me off for a few minutes, but then I thought about all of the times people have doubted me, said I wasn’t good enough, said I can’t do something that I wanted to do and how I’ve always channeled it and combined that with passion, hard work, and love to accomplish my goals. In posting this, I hope it encourages you guys to use negativity and spin it into a positive and don’t let anyone get you down or keep you from achieving your goals! Also, I’ve known @griffin_cola since he was a kid and I’m always happy to see people I know do well in life!!!!
#letsgo
